title: TOURNAMENT VOLLEYBALL | Tuesday’s matches
text:
The Tigers were eliminated from the Division II sectionals. 
Division III 
Garfield 25-23-25-25, Brookfield 13-25-18-11 
LEAVITTSBURG 
For the Warriors, Tori Sheehan had six kills and seven blocks, Katie Bender had 23 assists and 11 digs, and Bailey Drapola had 14 kills. 
Division IV 
Warren JFK 25-25-22-25, Newbury 22-19-25-18 
CORTLAND 
MacKayla Kroll had five kills, three aces, and one block for the Eagles, while Adrianna Placanica contributed 25 digs. Athena Burzynski also contributed two kills and one block, and Julia Lombradi tacked on six kills and one block for JFK. . 
St. Thomas Aquinas 25-25-25, Leetonia 13-10-7 
COLUMBIANA 
Aurora Smith had four kills and six digs, and Ariel Smith had nine assists and five digs for Leetonia. Katie Hiestand had 10 kills and two blocks, Nicole McGervey had 16 points and three aces, and Angela Farolina had 33 assists for St. Thomas Aquinas. East Canton 25-25-25, Heartland Christian 16-18-22 
COLUMBIANA 
Bonnie Flynn had 27 kills, eight points and 17 digs for the Lions, assisted by Brianna LaRocca, who had 27 assists and nine digs, and Alanna Holden, who had seven points, three aces, and four kills. For East Canton, Natalie Spitale had 29 digs, 14 kills, and four aces, Darian Ritchie had six blocks and 12 points, and Audriana Nichols had 15 assists. 
Staff report
